rComments: It's not his fault therwere no TAs. His class is dense. If you don't read and prepare, don't take him. If you do, listen and learn

He was the worst teacher ever. Horrible, vague exams. The final was 50% of the grade, and midterm was 40%, the other 10% was for a term paper that he didn't even grade. He didn't know how to do anything with the computer and was rude to students who answered questions wrong. He would stare off into space for like 10 sec between each sentence.

Incredibly unprofessional. It is standard procedure for him to show up 5-10 minutes late for class and let you out 15minutes early. He has long random pauses during his lectures. Could not work a computer if his life depended upon it. Review sheets are awful. To make the class "hard" he makes review sheets and review session vague and ambiguous.

One of the worst professors I have ever had. In his lectures, he practically reads his Powerpoints verbatim, and most of his it is composed of quotes from the text that we have read the night prior. He has no passion for teaching, and always arrive late to class. He also speaks slowly and makes the class a drag to attend.
Do not take this class if you don't like reading.

Such a ridiculous class. I took this because I thought it was going to be an easy gen ed and it is anything but that. Has potential to be interesting but he barely explains any of the difficult readings we have. Final is 50% of grade and midterm is 40%. Don't take this class!

The worse teacher I have ever had.  It is an easy class that he makes difficult.  He relies heavily on his TA for everything and makes himself as unavailable as possible.  I would never sign up for any of his classes.  I had to drop the class after the midterm because I got an F and this is a class where everyone assumes they will get an A.

A very poor excuse for an educator, Professor Rosas is an arrogant man with no interest in teaching. He assigns about 25 pages of reading per lecture and then only recites one or two points from each text in class. He speaks as if every word is its own sentence, constantly repeating himself. I guarantee that you will learn nothing in this class.

Everyone must go through his assistant with questions. I would advise not to take it with Rosas, plus the readings are long and sometimes he doesn't even talk about them. He wasn't very helpful at all and the entire grade is based on the midterm and the final

I started out in this class, and dropped it 3 weeks in. I felt like the prof was full of himself, and wasn't very pleasant in class. Class was boring the times I actually went, and tons of reading every day. I don't recommend this class with this prof, but I heard it was 'very easy' with Ellen Moodie.

i'm currently in this class with this professor. first of all he has been coming to class late. and then he want to end class early. so when we are going over reading in class i don't understand a thing he is taking about. I feel sorry for he asst. i think she is over worked. the reading sometimes are hard to understand.

Has no interest in teaching. Forbids students from e-mailing him. All correspondence must be through his assistant. Reads his power point nearly verbatim and barely elaborates on the topic. Complains about not having TAs to allow us to discuss the material and then ends class 20 minutes early.
Lectures are not captivating and he speaks very slow dragging out 10 minutes of material into a full class.
